{{Item|title=Bolt of Ophiotaurus|type=Weapon Ammunition|keywords=1 of 100|effects=If fired into a deity's eye, the deity loses invulnerability for 15 seconds|source=[[Benefactor Box]]}}
The '''Bolt of Ophiotaurus''' is a crossbow bolt that, if shot into a deity's eye, can strip the deity of its invulnerability for fifteen seconds. There are only (100) Bolts of Ophiotaurus available.
== AI Description == '''The Bolt of Ophiotaurus'''
'''This is 1 of 100.'''
'''This item acts as a regular crossbow bolt unless it is shot directly into the eye of a deity.'''
'''Upon a successful strike to the god’s eye, the deity’s invulnerability pauses for fifteen seconds.'''<ref>Dinniman, Matt. The Dungeon Anarchist's Cookbook: Dungeon Crawler Carl Book 3 (p. 433). Dandy House. Kindle Edition.</ref>
== Story == {{Spoiler | book = 3 | spoiler = [[Katia Grim]] receives the Bolt of Ophiotaurus in a [[Benefactor Box]] from [[Formidable|Princess Formidable]] of the [[The Skull Empire|Skull Empire]].}}
