{{citation}}
{{SpoilH | 6}}

Princess D'Nadia is a character outside the dungeon. Her first appearance is in Book 2. She is of the [[Saccathian]] race. She is princess of the [[Prism]]. Her Prism kingdom is small but Princess D'Nadia is a powerful force in trade circles and is quite outspoken. She is described as a squid-like, or like a human sized Cthulu. Her skin appears gray and covered in bumps, with a tangle of squid-like tentacles hanging from her face. 

Carl and Donut meet her on a roundtable show with [[Ripper Wonton]]. She becomes Princess Donut's sponsor during the 4th floor. She gifts Donut a [[Benefactor Box|benefactor box]] containing her glasses ([[Prism Industries Capacitating and Focusing Goggles]]). She sends Donut another benefactor box on the 5th floor that upgrades the goggles. She is next seen judging the Pet Beauty Contest and Talent Show at the [[Butcher's Masquerade]]. She informs Donut that her father passed away and she is now Empress D'Nadia. At the end of the Butcher's Masquerade, Carl learns that Empress D'Nadia has purchased a spot for [[Ninth Floor|faction wars]]. She ended her sponsorship of Donut on the [[Eighth Floor|8th Floor (Ghosts of Earth)]]. 



